<subSubSection lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="29.[189,1399,1787,2027]" lastBlockId="30.[234,1399,267,365]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis box="[189,855,1787,1813]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Bulletin of the Fan Memorial Institute of Biology, Botany</emphasis>
8: 31 (
<bibRefCitation author="Hu H. H." box="[936,1043,1787,1813]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="31 - 46" refId="ref36157" refString="Hu H. H. 1937. Notulae Systematicae ad Florem Sinensium. Bulletin of the Fan Memorial Institute of Biology, Botany 8: 31 - 46." type="journal article" year="1937">Hu 1937</bibRefCitation>
). – 
<typeStatus box="[1083,1146,1787,1813]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Type</typeStatus>
: 
<collectingCountry box="[1156,1229,1787,1813]" name="China" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1239,1332,1787,1813]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, Weisi Hsein, Yeh-Chih, 
<quantity box="[478,570,1823,1849]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="m" value="3400.0">3400 m</quantity>
a.s.l., 
<date box="[650,779,1822,1849]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1935-08">Aug. 1935</date>
, 
<emphasis box="[793,1008,1822,1849]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">C.W. Wang 68243</emphasis>
(lecto-, designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lin Q. &amp; Sun Q. &amp; Sun M. &amp; Li H. L." pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1247 - 1255" refId="ref37415" refString="Lin Q., Sun Q., Sun M. &amp; Li H. L. 2007. Lectotypifications of twenty-eight names of Chinese taxa in Angiospermae. Acta Botanica Boreali-Occidentalia Sinica 27 (6): 1247 - 1255." type="journal article" year="2007">
Lin 
<emphasis box="[1337,1399,1822,1848]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
2007: 1249
</bibRefCitation>
: PE01062681!; isolecto-: A00033785!, K000859895!, P01903232!, PE01062680!). – Note: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hu" authorityYear="1937" box="[308,490,1894,1920]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Corylus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wangii">
<emphasis box="[308,490,1894,1920]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Corylus wangii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recognized in the 
<emphasis box="[765,944,1894,1920]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Flora of 
<collectingCountry box="[872,944,1894,1920]" name="China" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">China</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Li P. - C. &amp; Skvortsov A. K." box="[960,1215,1894,1920]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="286 - 301" refId="ref37252" refString="Li P. - C. &amp; Skvortsov A. K. 1999. Betulaceae. In: Wu Z. Y. &amp; Raven P. H. (eds.) Flora of China 4: 286 - 301. Science Press, Beijing, and Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis." type="journal article" year="1999">Li &amp; Skvortsov 1999</bibRefCitation>
) and the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">World Checklist and Bibliography of Fagale</emphasis>
s (
<bibRefCitation author="Govaerts R. &amp; Frodin D. G." box="[720,1024,1929,1956]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref35520" refString="Govaerts R. &amp; Frodin D. G. 1998. World Checklist and Bibliography of Fagales (Betulaceae, Corylaceae, Fagaceae and Ticodendraceae). The Royal Botanic Gardens Kew, England." type="book" year="1998">Govaerts &amp; Frodin 1998</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Hu H. H." box="[1047,1237,1930,1956]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="141 - 152" refId="ref36186" refString="Hu H. H. 1948. Notulae Systematicae ad Floram Sinensem XI. Bulletin of the Fan Memorial Institute of Biology n. s. 1 (2): 141 - 152." type="journal article" year="1948">Hu (1948: 149)</bibRefCitation>
, on the other hand, regarded his species as synonymous to 
<taxonomicName authority="Decne. However" authorityName="Decne. However" authorityYear="1844" box="[782,1182,1965,1992]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Corylus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jacquemontii">
<emphasis box="[782,972,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">C. jacquemontii</emphasis>
Decne. However
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hu" authorityYear="1937" box="[1196,1313,1965,1991]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Corylus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wangii">
<emphasis box="[1196,1313,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">C. wangii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an involucre with many glandular trichomes, while 
<taxonomicName box="[803,977,2001,2027]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Corylus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jaquemontii">
<emphasis box="[803,977,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">C. jaquemontii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is eglandular. Both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Decne. However" authorityYear="1844" box="[1211,1398,2001,2027]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Corylus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jacquemontii">
<emphasis box="[1211,1398,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">C. jacquemontii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hu" authorityYear="1937" box="[286,403,268,294]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Corylus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wangii">
<emphasis box="[286,403,268,294]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. wangii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have long laciniate involucre apices, but these are sometimes divided in the latter. This latter character is very well developed in 
<taxonomicName box="[767,859,303,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Corylus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferox">
<emphasis box="[767,859,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. ferox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The involucre of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hu" authorityYear="1937" box="[1071,1184,303,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Corylus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wangii">
<emphasis box="[1071,1184,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. wangii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are thus strikingly similar to 
<emphasis box="[352,379,339,365]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C.</emphasis>
× 
<emphasis box="[408,533,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">spinescens</emphasis>
Rehder, an artificial hybrid between 
<taxonomicName box="[964,1201,338,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Corylus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ferox" variety="tibetica">
<emphasis box="[964,1057,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. ferox</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1113,1201,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">tibetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1257,1391,338,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Corylus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="avellana">
<emphasis box="[1257,1391,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. avellana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
